    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-02T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-02T13:00:00-05:00" n="309"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.00/3204: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-02T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 2, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>71. Department’s telegram No. 49 of June 21, 2 p.m. Could Department inform me
                    whether any decision has been reached and if so whether the announcement is to
                    be made following the meeting of the two Presidents.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
